  "text": "From this we see that c must have complex absolute value 1. Since c is real, c = ±1. Furthermore, we also note from Eq. (A.13) that 2(λ + µ) = n + 1, indicating that the loop P involved precisely (n + 1)/2 arrows going against the path, and thus, (n + 1)/2 arrows going along the path. This implies that the absence of central charge excludes Escheric loops [CITATION_1] .",
